text: Matej Ašanin (born 4 September 1993) is a Croatian handball player for RK Zagreb and the Croatian national team.EHF profile He represented Croatia at the 2020 European Men's Handball Championship.2020 European Men's Handball Championship squad ==References== ==External links== * Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Zagreb Category:Croatian male handball players Category:RK Zagreb players Category:CB Ademar León players Category:Liga ASOBAL players Category:Expatriate handball players Category:Croatian expatriate sportspeople in Portugal Category:Croatian expatriate sportspeople in Spain
